Stayed with Lindsay Smith the night before.  He is the director of SOSSA and leader of the trip.  Spent night before prepping birds and took train to Wollongong arriving at 1130pm.  Picked up by L. Smith and headed to his house for few beers before bed; up and to boat by 7am.  Australian Hobby flying around harbor.  Boat used is very old fishing vessell having seen better days - the Sandra K.  Lindsay wants to make t-shirts that say "I survived the Sandra K" - I can see why!  25 knot winds and big swell leaving harbor.  Very rough most of trip but not unpleasant!  Lots of birds helps. Over 1000 photographs taken.  Met Nikolass Hass (friend of friends who goes on many pelagics).  Got ride with him back to Sydney.  Made great stop at Royal National Park on way back and ended with beers and Thai Food in Sydney.	1 possible 'Snowy' according to L.
